race.comment: The well-related NOW IS THE HOUR (6) (full to G3 winner and G2 placed Inkaruna) placed over this track and trip last time out and will be ready to peak now third-up from the break. Gets the reliable Gollan/Jones combination and only needs some luck navigating from the sticky draw to be playing a major role in the outcome. ADRANOS (1) also hails from a handy family (half to G2 winner Tiamo Grace) and is a consistent conveyance who is yet to finish worse than fourth in nine career starts. Maps ideally for Maloney from gate two and another bold showing is expected. BLITZUM (3) has placed two of three over this course and distance and strips fitter second-up. In the mix. SILK SONIC (15) progressive mare who got off the mark last time with a 2.25 lengths victory over 1000m at Sunshine Coast. In the mix.
